cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.DS 

This paper presents a new machine learning model, the Weighted Tsetlin Machine, which is designed for pattern recognition and classification tasks. The paper discusses the model's ability to reduce computation time and memory usage by weighting the clauses, which suggests that it is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The model is also evaluated on image classification tasks (MNIST) and natural language processing tasks (IMDb), which suggests that it may be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
